Clear Title. To the extent that it is feasible and allowed by law, title to the property shall be cleared of all liens, taxes and other encumbrances prior to transfer or sale by the County to a qualified community development corporation or a qualified developer. The title may be cleared through:


Forgiveness of County liens as established in Section 17-126 of this article;



Cancellation of County-held tax certificates as allowed by state law;



Payment of liens;



Development of incentives for private, municipal and other governmental lienholders to release liens; or



By any other available means.
However, pursuant to Section 125.411 of the Florida Statutes, as amended, the County shall only convey the interest of the County and shall not warrant title.
